<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}+{y}={75}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}+{9}{y}={27}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{9},-{6}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --9. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{9}}{{-{{9}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{9}}}{{-{{9}}}}{\left(-{9}{x}+{1}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{9}}}{{-{{9}}}}{\left({75}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{9}\right)}{x}+-{1}{y}=-{75}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}+{9}{y}={27}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{y}=-{48}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{48}}{{8}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{6}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}+{1}{\left(-{6}\right)}={75}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}+{\left(-{6}\right)}={75}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}={75}-{\left(-{6}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}={81}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{81}}{{-{{9}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{9}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{9},-{6}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

